ğŸ”» FIVE TOP IDEAS IN THE WORLD
	1. Murphy's Law:	The more you fear sth happening, the more likely it is to happen
	2. Kidlin's Law:	If you can write the problem down clearly and specifically, then the matter is half solved
	3. Gilbert's Law:	The biggest Problem at work is that noone tells what you do
						when you take on a task, finding the best way to achieve the desired result is always your responsibility.
	4. Wilson's Law:	Prioritize: If you put information and intelligence first at all times, then the money keeps coming in
				You can't expect to hit the jackpot, if you don't put a few nickles in the machine
				Put value first, the money will follow.
	5. Falkland's Law:	When it is not necessary to make a decision, it is necessary not to make a decision
						if u dont have to make a decision about something, then dont decide.
	6. Pareto Principle	80/20: %80 of results come from 20% of effort; focus on the few actions that matter most
	7. Parkinson's Law	Work expands so as to fill the time available for its completion. procrastination
	8. Godwin's Law		as an online discussion grows longer, the probability of a comparison involving Nazis or Hitler approaches one
	9. Hick's Law		more choices mean slower decisions. reduce options to decide faster.


